## TL;DR — Blue Nile Three-Stone Engagement Rings 2026

**Setting price range:** $1,680 (Petite Three-Stone Lab-Grown Rose Gold) → $24,800 (Gallery Collection Vintage Trapezoid Yellow Gold)

**Most reviewed settings:**
- Classic Pear Shaped Sapphire in Platinum — **207 reviews** · [$2,610](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/classic-pear-shaped-sapphire-engagement-ring-in-platinum-item-194499?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blue_nile_reviews) *(side stones included in price)*
- Marquise Cut Diamond Three Stone (all metals) — **152 reviews each** · from [$1,970](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/marquise-cut-diamond-three-stone-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-by-james-allen-item-315103?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blue_nile_reviews)
- Trio Princess Cut Pavé — **73 reviews** · [$2,245](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/trio-princess-cut-pave-diamond-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-1-3-ct-tw-item-194393?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blue_nile_reviews)

[![Blue Nile Three Stone Past Present Future Rings](/images/bn-3stone-past-present-future.avif)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?styleIDs=three_stone&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blue_nile_reviews)

**Complete three-stone catalog:** [Browse all Blue Nile three-stone rings →](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?styleIDs=three_stone&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blue_nile_reviews)

**One-sentence verdict:** Blue Nile's three-stone catalog is the most diverse of any setting style — diamond, sapphire, ruby, baguette, marquise, lab-grown, and designer options across 60+ SKUs from $1,680 to $24,800 — and the answer to whether they're overpriced depends entirely on one thing: whether the side stones are included in the setting price (they are for sapphire and ruby settings) or purchased separately (they are for all-diamond settings).

---

## Who Wrote This

I'm [Farzana Hasan](https://diamondcritics.com/about-farzana/), GIA Expert and Lead Critic at Diamond Critics. Three-stone rings are consistently the second-most common anniversary and push present purchase — buyers come to this category with a symbolic reason, and Blue Nile's catalog is the broadest in online retail. This audit is organized by side stone type, which is the single most important decision in any three-stone ring purchase.

---

## Are Blue Nile Three-Stone Rings Overpriced? The Direct Answer

**It depends on what's in the price.** Two fundamentally different types of three-stone rings exist in this catalog:

**Type A — Gemstone side stones (price includes sapphire or ruby side stones).** The Classic Pear Shaped Sapphire Platinum setting at $2,610 includes two pear-shaped sapphire side stones. You are not paying $2,610 for a metal setting — you are paying for two gemstones and the metal together. At sapphire market prices, this represents fair value or better.

**Type B — Diamond side stones (setting price includes side diamonds, center purchased separately).** The Marquise Cut Diamond Three Stone at $1,970 includes two marquise-cut side diamonds. Your total cost is this setting price plus a loose center stone — the same as any solitaire or halo purchase at Blue Nile.

**The overpricing risk** is in the designer and Gallery Collection tiers ($5,000–$24,800 settings) where the included diamond weight is fixed but the setting design commands a significant premium over comparable weight in a plain prong setting. Whether that design premium is worth it is a matter of aesthetic preference, not objective pricing.

