Yellow gold ruby three-stone. The warm metal softens the ruby's vivid red, creating a richer, more tonal color effect. The red-gold combination reads as vintage Indian or Victorian jewelry in character.

**[Princess Cut Ruby Three Stone in 14K Rose Gold](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/princess-cut-ruby-three-stone-engagement-ring-in-14k-rose-gold-by-james-allen-item-310981?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blue_nile_reviews) — $2,410 · 3 reviews · Item #310981**
Rose gold ruby three-stone — the most unexpected colorway. The pink-red combination is unexpectedly harmonious; the similar hue register between rose gold and ruby creates a monochromatic warmth rather than stark contrast.

**[Princess Cut Ruby Three Stone in Platinum](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/princess-cut-ruby-three-stone-engagement-ring-in-platinum-by-james-allen-item-310980?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blue_nile_reviews) — $3,940 · 3 reviews · Item #310980**
Platinum ruby three-stone — $1,530 more than the 14k versions. Platinum's structural durability is worthwhile for ruby: the gemstone is harder than sapphire's corundum siblings, but princess-cut corners are vulnerable, and the $3,940 total for setting + two rubies + platinum construction is still reasonable.

