## Frequently Asked Questions

### Are Blue Nile three-stone engagement rings overpriced?

Not compared to solitaires of the same center weight. The setting prices ($1,680–$3,700 for standard catalog designs) include the side stones. A comparable solitaire setting runs $1,000–$1,355 — so you are paying approximately $600–$2,000 more for the setting but receiving two additional diamonds or gemstones as part of that price. The value question is whether you prefer the center stone alone or three stones together.

### What is the symbolism of a three-stone engagement ring?

The three stones traditionally represent past, present, and future. This symbolism makes three-stone rings the most common anniversary gift purchase and a frequent choice for push presents and milestone gifts — not just initial engagement rings. Blue Nile's three-stone catalog is broader than their solitaire catalog partly because of this multi-occasion demand.

### Which Blue Nile three-stone ring has the most reviews?

The [Classic Pear Shaped Sapphire Engagement Ring in Platinum](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/classic-pear-shaped-sapphire-engagement-ring-in-platinum-item-194499?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blue_nile_reviews) has 207 reviews — the highest count in the entire three-stone category. Among all-diamond settings, the Marquise Cut Three Stone has 152 reviews across each metal colorway.

### Do Blue Nile three-stone settings include the side stones?

Yes — all setting prices include the side stones. Whether they are diamonds, sapphires, or rubies, the side stones are part of the setting price. You purchase a loose center stone separately and have it set by Blue Nile.

### What is the cheapest three-stone engagement ring at Blue Nile?

The [Petite Three-Stone Lab-Grown Diamond Engagement Ring in 14K Rose Gold](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/petite-three-stone-lab-grown-diamond-engagement-ring-in-14k-rose-gold-item-309375?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blue_nile_reviews) at $1,680 is the lowest setting price in the catalog. Add a 1ct lab-grown G-VS2 center at approximately $700–$900 for a total ring cost under $2,600.

### What center stone works best in a Blue Nile three-stone ring?

Round brilliant is the safest choice — it works with every side stone shape. For marquise side stones, round centers create the most balanced silhouette. For baguette side stones, emerald-cut or cushion centers mirror the rectangular geometry. For pear sapphire side stones, round brilliant centers are the historically correct choice (per the original Diana/Kate design).
